Dear JJ Watt- First Id like to say I commend you for what you do on and off the field. Im a houston native born and raised and just like any other Houston sports fan the oilers were my favorite team. I guess I got it from my mom. She was a die hard fan till the team was sold. She and I like other houstonians grasped on the Cowboy train because they were a Texas team and my uncle's favorite. Shortly after my uncle's death in 97 it seemed like football was something none of us were interested in.....Until Houston acquired another team. The HOUSTON TEXANs. Now mom wasn't convinced those 1st few years, but the minute you sacked your 1st quarterback to all of your deflections she has become that die hard football fan we all know and love. She is your biggest support screaming louder than anyone in the stadium ... we always have to turn the TV up if you do something spectacular because she begins to yell ....WAAATTTT ??? WATTT? OMG  Shut you down became her go to phrase for the entire season last year. I say all this to say I know how much you love your mother and its probably just as much as I love mine. Last year was the 1st year in my 30+ years Ive ever been able to give my mother something nice for her birthday. She is also a fan of Hell's Kitchen so I was able to coordinate a dinner and meeting of Hell's Kitchen winner Ja'Nel Witt. She turned 55 wanted it to be special. Well her birthday is coming around again and with god blessing me with a better job, her job being a little rocky and unsure at times Id like to make this year better than the last and was hoping you could help me. She would probably never stop telling all her friends but If she could meet and maybe get a picture with you Im sure it would be something she could mark off her bucket list. She met her football hero... because that what you are to her. She literally gets upset if someone hits you to hard or they call a play against you. She is the ultimate fan. She is such a fan last year on my birthday she bought me these I hope you can help me make her 56th even more special than last year ...Mother's should look forward to wonderful birthdays and we as kids should do what we can to give them that one moment if thats all we can give. One moment of Joy she'll never forget .... I look forward to hearing from you. Please Help make my mom's dream come true Sept 30th 2015 üò™üò™
